just_use hand_stacks.go

# label: INTRICATE
# role: encodes domain knowledge

The "you already have 3+ cards that make a set or run" trick. Three
emit-order buckets: sets (by value), pure runs (by suit), rb runs.
Matches TS iteration order so first_play is stable across impls.

Double-deck wrinkles:
- Sets: pickValidSet takes the first card seen per distinct suit; later
  same-suit duplicates are skipped (can't have two Kings of Hearts in
  one set).
- Pure runs + rb runs: dedup by value (no two same-value cards in a run,
  even from different decks).

isValidGroup is a defensive check — the shape finder can produce
candidates that GetStackType still rejects, and we'd rather re-validate
than produce a Bogus Play.
